 Pakistan, Lebanon, Libya, and Nigeria. Klausen shows how the cartoon crisis was, therefore, ultimately a political conflict rather than a colossal cultural misunderstanding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBlasphemy (Islam)vCase studies. 0aCaricatures and cartoonsxPolitical aspectszDenmark. 0aCaricatures and cartoonsxPolitical aspectszIslamic countries. 0aChristianity and other religionsxIslamvCase studies. 0aMuslimszDenmarkxPolitics and governmenty21st century. 0aProtest movementszDenmarkxHistoryy21st century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 21st Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015506840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300155068423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300155068/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles